__3 Cents__ - Figure 3. illustrates on entire letter from Penang addressed to Calcutta, India, bearing a 3-cent stamp and struck with the Penang 147 diamond of ten cancellation dated October 2, 1867. The diamond of ten duplex cancellation was the last cancellation used during the Indian Administration.
Penang "147 Diamond of Ten" Duplex Cancellation
The Penang 147 duplex was first recorded on July 23, 1863 and the latest specimen seen was dated October 24, 1867 (as illustrated in Fig. 6). Singapore was also allotted one with the '172' 
numeral, but very few covers survived (N.B: I know of only 2 such covers.)
