</p>

</div>
<div style="width:48%;float:left">
<img src="http://localhost/egypt/straights/SG10-03.jpg" style="width:98%;margin-right:10px;display:block"  >
<p style="font-size:smaller">

Sale 4010 Lot 42 Sale 4010 Lot 42. 19 Jun 2004 10:30 Singapore 

STRAITS SETTLEMENTS
1869 (?) "2" in manuscript on 11/2c. on 1/2a. blue, neatly cancelled by part blue duplex; one pulled perf at foot otherwise fine used. Rare. Sc. 9A; S.G. 10, £4250. Photo
Estimate S$ 7,000-9,000 
</p>

</div>

These provisional probably used early 1869 were used to alleviate a shortage of the 
2-cent postage stamps. They are ususally associated with the Penang D17 duplex cancellation. They can be found with blue colour and they are considered to be used in Penang. Two types are identified.

